<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rowland" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rowland,</orth> name of 1) the most famous of Charlemagne's peers: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 187</bibl>. 2) Sir R. de Boys, the father of Oliver and Orlando in <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.235" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 235</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.235" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.235" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 235</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.191" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 7, 191</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.158" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 158</bibl>. 3) a person mentioned in <bibl n="shak. mm 4.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 5, 8</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>